	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Thu Dec 19, 2013 5:38 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Final Fantasy VII NES Project Completed</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Mapper 34 with &lt;=8K CHR, as implemented by emulators following the guidance on the wiki, is equivalent to a 74HC377 (octal D flip-flop) for holding the bank number and a 74HC20 (dual 4-input NOR) for decoding a 6264 SRAM at $6000 and avoiding bus conflicts. Some other emulators will keep the NINA ports at $7FFD-$7FFF active even with &lt;=8K CHR.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
